	Ford ties the knot    
	 June 17: Actors Harrison Ford, 67, and Calista Flockhart, 45, have tied the knot in a wedding presided over by New Mexicos governor, reports The Daily Telegraph.      
	Gov. Bill Richardson said that the couple, who have been together for several years and got engaged last year, were married at the governors mansion in Santa Fe. Richardson presided over the ceremony on Tuesday afternoon at the mansion on a hilltop along the northern edge of Santa Fe.       
	Richardson has played host at the mansion to Spanish royalty, North Korean diplomats and other Hollywood stars, but this marked the first wedding there during his tenure.    
	Tom Atlas     
	 London (PTI): Actor Tom Hanks is planning to star in a major role in the movie adaptation of Cloud Altas with Halle Berry and James McAvoy. The big screen adaptation of David Mitchells acclaimed novel is being directed by Tom Tykwer. Sir Ian McKellan and Natalie Portman have also been linked to the project.    
	Jen swing    
	 Los Angeles (PTI): After starring as a foul-mouthed dentist in Horrible Bosses, Jennifer Aniston is all set to play a raunchy role in Wanderlust. Aniston, 41, will be seen swearing, stripping and swinging in the movie which also stars actor Paul Rudd, reports Us magazine. They play a New York couple who long for a home of their own, but because of the economy, they reluctantly settle for living with his obnoxious brother in Georgia.     
	Paris club    
	Los Angeles (PTI): Socialite Paris Hilton is reportedly dating night club owner Cy Waits in secret and has been spending a lot of time in Las Vegas lately. Hilton, 29, who split with The Hills star Doug Reinhardt in April, has been flying out to Vegas often to be with Waits, who manages a number of hot spots with his twin brother, Jesse.    
